   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Predator-prey system\n",
    "\n",
    "We encode the predator–prey equations via a function."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "using FundamentalsNumericalComputation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "predprey (generic function with 1 method)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "function predprey(u,p,t)\n",
    "    α,β = p;  y,z = u;      # rename for convenience\n",
    "    s = (y*z) / (1+β*y)     # appears in both equations\n",
    "    return [ y*(1-α*y) - s,  -z + s ]\n",
    "end"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note that the function accepts three inputs, `u`, `p`, and `t`, even though there is no explicit dependence on `t`. The second input is used to pass parameters that don't change throughout a single instance of the problem. \n",
    "\n",
    "To solve the IVP we must also provide the initial condition, which is a 2-vector here, and the interval for the independent variable."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "u0 = [1,0.01]\n",
    "tspan = (0.,80.)\n",
    "α,β = 0.1,0.25\n",
    "\n",
    "ivp = ODEProblem(predprey,u0,tspan,[α,β])\n",
    "sol = solve(ivp);"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "@show size(sol.u);\n",
    "@show (sol.t[20],sol.u[20]);\n",
    "\n",
    "u = [ sol.u[i][j] for i=1:length(sol.t), j=1:2 ]\n",
    "scatter!(sol.t,u,m=3,label=\"\")"
   ]
